snippet: A Cairo court on Thursday found four senior policemen not guilty of killing protesters during last year’s popular uprising.
abstract: Cairo court finds four senior policemen not guilty of killing protesters during the 2011 popular uprising in Egypt, the latest acquittal of officials charged in connection with the more than 800 deaths during the crackdown.
lead_paragraph: A Cairo court on Thursday found four senior policemen not guilty of killing protesters during last year’s popular uprising.
